public interface Definition<E extends Definition<E,P,S,F>,P extends DeclarationContainer,S extends Signature,F extends Declaration>
extends Declaration<E,P,S,F>

A definition is a declaration that needs a definition. Examples are methods and types. A variable is not a definition because it is always complete.
